<span title>Data Base</span>
<pre zoom labels = "database.introduction, database.definitions">
<div tagcount></div>
<span xsmall>Data Base Definition</span>
Organized collection of structured related information, or data, typically stored in a computer.
The data is managed by a DBMS(DataBase Management System).

Example of DB:
+---------+
|Data type|
+---+-----+  +------------+
    |      +-+----------+ |
    +----> |Folder Names+-+
           +-----+------+    +---------------+
                 |         +--------------+  |
                 |       +-+------------+-|- +
                 +------>| Data & Signal+-+
                         |    Names     |
                         +--------------+
</pre>

<pre zoom labels = "database.introduction, database.definitions, database.DMBS">
<div tagcount></div>
<span xsmall>DBMS</span>
Software to ease:
-->Define the Data Base.
-->Construction of Data Base.
-->Handling of Data Base.
</pre>

<pre zoom labels = "database.introduction, database.definitions, database.DMBS">
<div tagcount></div>
<span xsmall>DBMS Functions</span>
1.Allow users to create Data Bases and specify the schemes using DDL(Data Definition Language).
2.Allow users to view and modify data using DML(Data Manipulation Language).
3.Allow the storage large volumes of data and an efficient access.
4.Allow the crash recovery of the DB.
5.Transaction management for concurrent access.
</pre>


